item.description:
Nana&rsquo;s final advice to Raghoba, after pAnIpaT.
&ldquo;Do not abandon the righteous path or ethical conduct. If Marathas or Muslims behave as per the traditions of their caste or community, do not discriminate against them. The Kingdom should not discriminate on the basis of the person&rsquo;s faith or his deity&rdquo;
Hindu Marathe, Musalman yaani aaple aaple reetine vartalyas dvesh sahasa konhe hi jaaticha na karava, va jyacha jo dharm, jyache je daivat tyaaj vishaii dvesh rajya neetis nasava
